Chad F. Wolf is currently serving as the Acting Secretary of the Department of Homeland Security (DHS), overseeing the third largest department in the US federal government. He is responsible for various areas including counterterrorism, border security, immigration enforcement, response to disasters, and cybersecurity. Prior to his current position, Wolf served as the first Under Secretary of the DHS Office of Strategy, Policy, and Plans. He has also held roles as Chief of Staff and Assistant Secretary for DHS, as well as Chief of Staff for the Transportation Security Administration. Wolf has received recognition for his leadership and management skills, including the United States Secretary of Homeland Security Distinguished Service Medal. Before working in government, he spent 11 years in the private sector and also worked on Capitol Hill as a staffer.